{
  "answer": "**The work is *Kalpabuddha* (author unknown), Chapter 1.**[^1]\n\nThe cosmogonic opening declares:  \n> Lord Buddha was in the great dissolution (`mahāpralaya`), his body came into being, he then became the Lord Pañcatathāgata.[^2]\n\nIt then describes the central Tathāgata of this fivefold body as follows:  \n> His `mudrā` is the `bodhyagrī`, his `jñāna` is `śāśvata`, his implement is the `cakra`. Sahāvatī is the name of his dominion, a lion is his mount. She, Lady Sattvavajrī, she, Lady Dharmavajrī, she, Lady Karmavajrī, they are the `devī`s accompanying him.[^2]\n\n[^1]: *Kalpabuddha*, [Chapter 1](/works/unknown-kalpabuddha-d760dc/01/translation/).\n[^2]: *Kalpabuddha*, [Chapter 1, paragraph p-e1c8df](/works/unknown-kalpabuddha-d760dc/01/translation/#p-e1c8df).",
